  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b89\u0bb2\u0b95\u0bb5\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba4\u0bc8  \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0baf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b86\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "After the World Bank refused to provide anything, Sri Lanka opened negotiations with the International Monetary Fund",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka has resumed negotiations with the International Monetary Fund on Friday following the World Bank's announcement that it will not provide funds to the country until it implements deep structural changes.",
        "The island nation of Sri Lanka has reached bankruptcy and its economy is in a death spiral.",
        "New data released on Friday revealed that inflation stood at 60.8 percent in July.",
        "These reports have come out even as reports have surfaced that China is sending a ship to the Ambantota port leased by China to Sri Lanka. India is concerned about China's base in its backyard.",
        "India has provided 4 billion dollars in financial aid to Sri Lanka this year alone. China is seen as the country that has given the most credit to Sri Lanka.",
        "Sri Lanka's 22 million people have been facing months of food and fuel shortages due to rising inflation and frequent power cuts.",
        "Sri Lanka defaulted on $51 billion in debt in April, and massive protests led to the ouster this month of former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa, who fled the country before resigning.",
        "The World Bank has stated that it is concerned about the situation of the people of Sri Lanka and said in its statement that it cannot provide financing to Sri Lanka until an adequate economic structure is established.",
        "The World Bank, which has called for deep structural changes focused on economic stability, has said that solutions must be found to the underlying problems that created the crisis.",
        "And the World Bank has set aside 160 million dollars of its loans to provide urgent needs such as medicine, cooking gas, food for school students, etc.",
        "Sri Lanka is also in the process of establishing a viable government once again Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe has been sworn in as president and the opposition is trying to reach an agreement to form a comprehensive government to replace the previous government."
      ],
